1
00:00:04,005 --> 00:00:06,941
⟨Famous transgender novelist and bar mom→

2
00:00:07,008 --> 00:00:09,944
My dear partner, a housewife, is⟩

3
00:00:10,010 --> 00:00:12,446
(Masayoshi) I don't know my password, so please help me solve it.

4
00:00:12,513 --> 00:00:14,949
(Luna) Is this his computer?

5
00:00:15,015 --> 00:00:17,451
⟨To solve the password of a closed computer →

6
00:00:17,518 --> 00:00:20,955
Traveling around Tokyo relying on literature⟩

7
00:00:21,021 --> 00:00:22,957
(Misato) Help me, come right away!

8
00:00:23,023 --> 00:00:26,460
⟨Luna is upset when her mother suddenly asks her for help⟩

9
00:00:26,527 --> 00:00:27,962
(Bubbly) Wait!

10
00:00:28,029 --> 00:00:31,532
⟨Episode 8 just below the sudden turn Don't miss it⟩

11
00:00:39,039 --> 00:00:41,475
(unlock sound)

12
00:00:41,542 --> 00:00:53,487
♪～

13
00:00:53,554 --> 00:00:56,991
Ah! Who is it!?

14
00:00:57,057 --> 00:00:59,060
(Sound of running) Ahhh!

15
00:01:05,499 --> 00:01:09,437
(Misato) Luna-san. (Luna) Huh... Mother.

16
00:01:09,503 --> 00:01:12,940
>> That was quick. (Luna) Even though you were injured.

17
00:01:13,007 --> 00:01:14,942
>>I think it's a mild sprain.

18
00:01:15,009 --> 00:01:17,945
The pain has subsided, so I don't think I should worry.

19
00:01:18,012 --> 00:01:19,947
(Luna) Sprain?

20
00:01:20,014 --> 00:01:24,452
>> I was so nervous! I thought it broke.

21
00:01:24,518 --> 00:01:28,456
That's right, Luna-san, why don't we go to a beauty salon together?

22
00:01:28,522 --> 00:01:30,958
(Luna) I can't go. I'm going home now.

23
00:01:31,025 --> 00:01:34,528
Excuse me, please put on your shoes.

24
00:01:40,534 --> 00:01:42,536
(Ryoko) Huh?

25
00:01:46,540 --> 00:01:48,976
(Ryoko) Bubbly-chan. (Bubbly) Wow!

26
00:01:49,043 --> 00:01:50,978
(Ryoko) What are you doing?

27
00:01:51,045 --> 00:01:54,482
>> I can't go home for a while... (Ryoko) Huh?

28
00:01:54,548 --> 00:01:57,485
>>That's my apartment...

29
00:01:57,551 --> 00:02:00,488
(Ryoko) Oh, is that so? Close to home!

30
00:02:00,554 --> 00:02:02,990
>> Ah sh~ sh~ sh~…｡

31
00:02:08,996 --> 00:02:11,432
Kill time somewhere.

32
00:02:11,499 --> 00:02:13,934
Sorry for showing you something weird.

33
00:02:14,001 --> 00:02:16,504
(Ryoko) No. >> Well then.

34
00:02:23,511 --> 00:02:31,018
📱(vibration sound)

35
00:02:33,020 --> 00:02:35,956
(Ryoko) Bubbly-chan.

36
00:02:36,023 --> 00:02:38,459
Can I come home if you like?

37
00:02:38,526 --> 00:02:39,960
>> Huh?

38
00:02:40,027 --> 00:02:44,465
I'm sorry I had to cancel the hot spring.

39
00:02:44,532 --> 00:02:46,467
(Luna) It's already late so I gave up.

40
00:02:46,534 --> 00:02:48,969
>> Then, would you like to eat at home?

41
00:02:49,036 --> 00:02:50,971
(Luna) Because there isn't.

42
00:02:51,038 --> 00:02:53,974
>> But you're hungry, right?

43
00:02:54,041 --> 00:02:56,544
Go eat something somewhere!

44
00:03:00,548 --> 00:03:02,550
📱(notification sound)

45
00:03:07,488 --> 00:03:11,425
(Ryoko) Wow... Oh no, that's scary.

46
00:03:11,492 --> 00:03:14,495
(Aromatic) I'm home. (Ryoko) Welcome back.

47
00:03:15,996 --> 00:03:17,998
>> I'm bothering you.

48
00:03:21,001 --> 00:03:24,438
After all, if you stir-fry the onions well, you'll get a lot of flavor.

49
00:03:24,505 --> 00:03:27,942
(Aromatic) Yes, it's delicious!

50
00:03:28,008 --> 00:03:31,445
Atsushi: I'm too nervous.

51
00:03:31,512 --> 00:03:35,449
(Atsushi) No, it's real? It's my first time meeting someone...

52
00:03:35,516 --> 00:03:37,952
(Ryoko) It's real.

53
00:03:38,018 --> 00:03:40,955
>> What do you think? Come meet the real thing.

54
00:03:41,021 --> 00:03:43,958
It's beautiful. I was really surprised.

55
00:03:44,024 --> 00:03:46,460
happy! thank you.

56
00:03:46,527 --> 00:03:48,462
Why is the name Bubbly?

57
00:03:48,529 --> 00:03:50,464
Because I like soap bubbles.

58
00:03:50,531 --> 00:03:53,467
(Ryoko) Hey, this is my first time hearing it! Fufufu…｡

59
00:03:53,534 --> 00:03:56,470
>> Real name is Ritsu. The law's "Ritsu."

60
00:03:56,537 --> 00:03:58,973
(Aromatic) Well then, it's Ricchan. That's right!

61
00:03:59,039 --> 00:04:01,976
Which foundation do you use?

62
00:04:02,042 --> 00:04:03,911
I'm looking for someone with covering power.

63
00:04:03,978 --> 00:04:05,913
I've been curious about my freckles lately.

64
00:04:05,980 --> 00:04:08,415
There is also a way to show it rather than hide it.

65
00:04:08,482 --> 00:04:11,919
I also think this mole is a charm point.

66
00:04:11,986 --> 00:04:14,922
I always look in the mirror and say, ``I saw Orion!''

67
00:04:14,989 --> 00:04:18,425
(Ryoko) Ah, that's true! >> So cute.

68
00:04:18,492 --> 00:04:23,430
I see... Do you understand both men's feelings and women's feelings?

69
00:04:23,497 --> 00:04:25,933
I don't know how a man feels.

70
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:28,435
The only thing that made him a man was his body.

71
00:04:28,502 --> 00:04:31,438
I've always been a girl at heart.

72
00:04:31,505 --> 00:04:33,941
You don't know anything.

73
00:04:34,008 --> 00:04:35,442
Sorry.

74
00:04:35,509 --> 00:04:37,945
It's natural that you wouldn't know if you weren't around.

75
00:04:38,012 --> 00:04:42,449
That's why I'm grateful to be able to talk to you like this.

76
00:04:42,516 --> 00:04:47,021
📱(vibration sound)

77
00:04:48,522 --> 00:04:50,958
Do I have to go out? >>Yes.

78
00:04:51,025 --> 00:04:53,460
Oh, try eating this.

79
00:04:53,527 --> 00:04:57,965
(Luna) It's rare for me to go to a spa, even though I don't usually go out much.

80
00:04:58,032 --> 00:05:01,969
>> Ma-kun said to me, ``Why don't you take a break once in a while?''

81
00:05:02,036 --> 00:05:05,406
Ma-kun is a really good boy.

82
00:05:05,472 --> 00:05:09,910
(Luna) What is that computer you brought Ma-kun?

83
00:05:09,977 --> 00:05:12,413
(Misato) Did you know the password?

84
00:05:12,479 --> 00:05:14,415
(Luna) Answer the question.

85
00:05:14,481 --> 00:05:16,917
>>You as a child→

86
00:05:16,984 --> 00:05:20,921
You and your father used to solve riddles together in ``The Little Prince.''

87
00:05:20,988 --> 00:05:24,925
What was the correct answer?

88
00:05:24,992 --> 00:05:29,430
(Luna) I think it was a hiding place for birthday presents.

89
00:05:29,496 --> 00:05:34,435
>>In other words, I guess that's the case with that computer as well.

90
00:05:34,501 --> 00:05:36,437
(Luna) Is that what you mean?

91
00:05:36,503 --> 00:05:38,939
>> It means nothing if you don't open it.

92
00:05:39,006 --> 00:05:41,008
(Luna) That's not an answer.

93
00:05:42,509 --> 00:05:44,445
>> Hey Luna-san.

94
00:05:44,511 --> 00:05:48,515
Why don't you show your face at home soon?

95
00:05:51,018 --> 00:05:53,954
Even my father doesn't say it out loud.

96
00:05:54,021 --> 00:05:57,958
I think you're worried about Luna.

97
00:05:58,025 --> 00:06:00,461
(Luna) Do you think we can meet?

98
00:06:00,527 --> 00:06:03,397
Besides, that person must be busy too.

99
00:06:03,464 --> 00:06:07,401
>> Not really. The director has also retired.

100
00:06:07,468 --> 00:06:09,403
(Luna) Eh, why?

101
00:06:09,470 --> 00:06:13,907
>> It's already a good year.

102
00:06:13,974 --> 00:06:18,912
Starting this spring, the vice director became the director.

103
00:06:18,979 --> 00:06:21,482
We don't have an heir.

104
00:06:23,484 --> 00:06:26,920
Ah, I'm not blaming you.

105
00:06:26,987 --> 00:06:32,426
I think it's best for children to live their own lives.

106
00:06:32,493 --> 00:06:36,930
On the contrary, I continued to put that kind of pressure on →

107
00:06:36,997 --> 00:06:39,500
I feel sorry.

108
00:06:41,001 --> 00:06:44,438
And dad →

109
00:06:44,505 --> 00:06:47,941
I haven't been feeling very well lately.

110
00:06:48,008 --> 00:06:50,944
(Luna) If that's the case, there's no way I can go that extra mile.

111
00:06:51,011 --> 00:06:55,449
When the son who left becomes a daughter and comes back →

112
00:06:55,516 --> 00:06:58,452
Your health will only get worse.

113
00:06:58,519 --> 00:07:02,456
>> So how long are you going to stay silent?

114
00:07:02,523 --> 00:07:06,960
(Luna) I have already left the Nomiya family.

115
00:07:10,464 --> 00:07:12,900
>> What a wonderful family.

116
00:07:12,966 --> 00:07:15,903
The children are very good children.

117
00:07:15,969 --> 00:07:19,406
(Ryoko) Did those kids say anything rude?

118
00:07:19,473 --> 00:07:21,408
>> It's okay.

119
00:07:21,475 --> 00:07:24,411
(Ryoko) I get worried sometimes too.

120
00:07:24,478 --> 00:07:26,914
Unconsciously, mom and Bubbly-chan →

121
00:07:26,980 --> 00:07:29,416
Did you say anything that would hurt me?

122
00:07:29,483 --> 00:07:33,420
>> If that happens, just say it properly and it's okay.

123
00:07:33,487 --> 00:07:36,924
In 10 years, the world will be easier for everyone to live in →

124
00:07:36,990 --> 00:07:40,427
I think it would be nice if that happened.

125
00:07:40,494 --> 00:07:44,932
(Ryoko) Yeah, I hope so.

126
00:07:44,998 --> 00:07:48,936
>> Well then, thank you for your meal today.

127
00:07:49,002 --> 00:07:52,506
(Ryoko) See you soon, good night. >> Good night.

128
00:07:57,010 --> 00:08:00,948
Hey, would you like to go eat Anne of Green Gables sweets next time?

129
00:08:01,014 --> 00:08:02,449
(Luna) What is that?

130
00:08:02,516 --> 00:08:06,386
>>They're holding a fair at Hotel Verdia right now.

131
00:08:06,453 --> 00:08:11,391
I loved you, Anne of Green Gables.

132
00:08:11,458 --> 00:08:14,394
I can't see the schedule.

133
00:08:14,461 --> 00:08:16,897
The good thing about Ann is →

134
00:08:16,964 --> 00:08:21,401
It's about trying to turn anxiety into hope.

135
00:08:21,468 --> 00:08:27,908
``Tomorrow is a new day where we haven't failed at anything yet.''

136
00:08:27,975 --> 00:08:29,910
Good words.

137
00:08:29,977 --> 00:08:32,479
I wish you could learn from me too.

138
00:08:39,486 --> 00:08:43,423
(Mami's voice) ``I'm in front of Ricchan's house now.''

139
00:08:43,490 --> 00:08:48,495
I'm sorry I couldn't meet you, but next time I'll contact you before I go."

140
00:08:53,500 --> 00:08:55,435
(Misato) Ah, welcome back.

141
00:08:55,502 --> 00:08:57,938
I just got back too. (Eisuke) Ah.

142
00:08:58,005 --> 00:09:01,508
Today I met that girl for the first time in a while.

143
00:09:04,945 --> 00:09:07,881
Ah... how was the farewell party?

144
00:09:07,948 --> 00:09:11,385
(Eisuke) Yeah, well...｡

145
00:09:11,451 --> 00:09:27,968
♪～

146
00:09:31,204 --> 00:09:33,140
(Ryoko) Yes, I forgot this.

147
00:09:33,206 --> 00:09:37,144
>>Thank you, I only realized this when I got home.

148
00:09:37,210 --> 00:09:39,646
(Kominato) It's a great coincidence that we're in the same town.

149
00:09:39,713 --> 00:09:42,149
(Ryoko) Hey, it's strange that we haven't met until now.

150
00:09:42,215 --> 00:09:44,151
(Meguru) We ran into each other and went to dinner →

151
00:09:44,217 --> 00:09:46,153
Have you had a feast?

152
00:09:46,219 --> 00:09:49,656
(Bubbly) Well, there are a lot of things going on. (Luna) A lot of things?

153
00:09:49,723 --> 00:09:52,659
>> Mami suddenly came to my house.

154
00:09:52,726 --> 00:09:56,229
(Luna) Mami-san Is that Mami-san?

155
00:09:57,731 --> 00:10:01,168
>> That girl is my childhood friend from the countryside.

156
00:10:01,234 --> 00:10:03,170
(Mami) [Aiko right]

157
00:10:03,236 --> 00:10:05,172
[Ricchan wins]

158
00:10:05,238 --> 00:10:08,675
(Bubly's voice) She's like a sister, 8 years younger than me. >> [Chiyoko Late]

159
00:10:08,742 --> 00:10:11,678
(Bubly's voice) The child's mother, who was busy with work, asked me to do it.→

160
00:10:11,745 --> 00:10:14,181
You took good care of me.

161
00:10:14,247 --> 00:10:19,186
He was always following me and was so cute.

162
00:10:19,252 --> 00:10:22,189
Even after I left the countryside →

163
00:10:22,255 --> 00:10:25,692
We've only been exchanging emails for a long time, but...

164
00:10:25,759 --> 00:10:30,697
We have never met in person in the 18 years since we broke up.

165
00:10:30,764 --> 00:10:34,701
Mami doesn't even know that I had the surgery.

166
00:10:34,768 --> 00:10:37,704
That girl still thinks about me →

167
00:10:37,771 --> 00:10:40,774
I think he's my childhood friend's brother.

168
00:10:44,277 --> 00:10:46,213
(Ryoko) Wow, cute girl.

169
00:10:46,279 --> 00:10:48,215
Is this person your boyfriend?

170
00:10:48,281 --> 00:10:51,218
>> Fiance: We've decided to get married.

171
00:10:51,284 --> 00:10:55,655
They said they were going to have a wedding in Tokyo and wanted you to come.

172
00:10:55,722 --> 00:10:59,159
When I replied that I was absent, he barged into my house.

173
00:10:59,226 --> 00:11:01,161
(Ryoko) Ah, that's right.

174
00:11:01,228 --> 00:11:06,166
>>Actually, I would like to say "congratulations" directly→

175
00:11:06,233 --> 00:11:08,668
Because I can't meet you.

176
00:11:08,735 --> 00:11:12,172
(Meguru) I also cut off all my old friends.

177
00:11:12,239 --> 00:11:14,674
(Kominato) Eh, everyone, is that what it's like?

178
00:11:14,741 --> 00:11:19,679
It depends on the person, but I think there are a lot of people around me like that.

179
00:11:19,746 --> 00:11:22,182
I've never been to a class reunion.

180
00:11:22,249 --> 00:11:24,184
(Ryoko) That's right...

181
00:11:24,251 --> 00:11:27,187
>> Where will the ceremony be held?

182
00:11:27,254 --> 00:11:29,689
I think it was Hotel Verdia.

183
00:11:29,756 --> 00:11:32,192
Ah, I went there the other day!

184
00:11:32,259 --> 00:11:36,263
We're currently holding an ``Anne of Green Gables'' sweets fair.

185
00:11:38,765 --> 00:11:41,768
[Would you like to go eat Anne of Green Gables sweets next time? ]

186
00:11:43,770 --> 00:11:45,705
(Kominato) Are you okay?

187
00:11:45,772 --> 00:11:49,209
(Meguru) They're all sweets that appear in "Anne of Green Gables."

188
00:11:49,276 --> 00:11:52,712
(Ryoko) Hey, I didn't read much though →

189
00:11:52,779 --> 00:11:55,148
I loved "Anne of Green Gables".

190
00:11:55,215 --> 00:11:59,152
>> I've never read it. What's the story about?

191
00:11:59,219 --> 00:12:01,154
(Ryoko) Good to hear from you.

192
00:12:01,221 --> 00:12:04,658
Mom, please. (Luna) Eh, me?

193
00:12:04,724 --> 00:12:06,726
(Ryoko) Please.

194
00:12:09,729 --> 00:12:13,166
(Luna) "Anne of Green Gables" was written by Canadian author Montgomery →

195
00:12:13,233 --> 00:12:16,169
A work published in 1908.

196
00:12:16,236 --> 00:12:20,173
Although it is famous as children's literature, it is suitable for both children and adults →

197
00:12:20,240 --> 00:12:23,677
A masterpiece loved by people of all ages around the world.

198
00:12:23,743 --> 00:12:26,680
The setting is Prince Edward Island.

199
00:12:26,746 --> 00:12:31,685
An elderly brother and sister who were planning to adopt a working boy from an orphanage →

200
00:12:31,751 --> 00:12:34,688
The person who came to Matthew and Marilla by mistake is →

201
00:12:34,754 --> 00:12:37,190
It was Anne, a red-haired girl.

202
00:12:37,257 --> 00:12:39,693
Anne, who loves daydreaming and is talkative, →

203
00:12:39,759 --> 00:12:42,195
After various encounters and events →

204
00:12:42,262 --> 00:12:45,265
It's a story of growing up.

205
00:12:47,267 --> 00:12:51,705
>> Anne has a bit of the same image as Mami.

206
00:12:51,771 --> 00:12:55,642
I bet she looks beautiful as a bride.

207
00:12:55,709 --> 00:12:57,711
I wanted to see it.

208
00:13:03,717 --> 00:13:05,652
(Ryoko) For example →

209
00:13:05,719 --> 00:13:09,656
What do you mean by just going to see it from a distance?

210
00:13:09,723 --> 00:13:11,158
>> Huh?

211
00:13:11,224 --> 00:13:15,162
(Ryoko) If you don't feel comfortable going alone, you can go with me.

212
00:13:15,228 --> 00:13:17,164
I want to eat Anne's sweets.

213
00:13:17,230 --> 00:13:19,666
If Bubbly-chan changes her mind during the process→

214
00:13:19,733 --> 00:13:23,236
You can just eat sweets and come home.

215
00:13:29,743 --> 00:13:32,179
>> I think I'll go...

216
00:13:32,245 --> 00:13:36,183
Ryoko-san, will you really go out with me?

217
00:13:36,249 --> 00:13:38,251
(Ryoko) Of course!

218
00:13:40,754 --> 00:13:44,758
(Kominato) I'm going to go shopping. (Ryoko) Come on in.

219
00:13:47,761 --> 00:13:52,699
(Luna) Mami-san is special to Bubbly-chan.

220
00:13:52,766 --> 00:13:56,136
I feel like we're a real family.

221
00:13:56,203 --> 00:14:01,141
(Ryoko) Even if someone is so important to me, I can't meet them.

222
00:14:01,208 --> 00:14:06,146
(Luna) There are many reasons why you can't meet old acquaintances.

223
00:14:06,213 --> 00:14:10,650
(Luna's voice) Some people feel sad because they remember times when life was difficult.

224
00:14:10,717 --> 00:14:15,155
Some people let go of their past in order to live a new life.

225
00:14:15,222 --> 00:14:20,160
In some cases, the difficulty of getting people to understand is ingrained in them.

226
00:14:20,227 --> 00:14:22,162
(Ryoko) Ah...｡

227
00:14:22,229 --> 00:14:27,667
(Luna) Me too When I met Mr. Tamura again in Osaka →

228
00:14:27,734 --> 00:14:30,170
To be honest, I braced myself for a moment.

229
00:14:30,237 --> 00:14:34,174
(Tamura) [What!? Noppy? Himself? ]

230
00:14:34,241 --> 00:14:36,176
[Huh? Seriously?]

231
00:14:36,243 --> 00:14:39,679
(Luna) [Seriously, I'm Noppy]

232
00:14:39,746 --> 00:14:43,683
(Luna's voice) I was so happy back then.

233
00:14:43,750 --> 00:14:46,186
I was grateful.

234
00:14:46,253 --> 00:14:49,689
If Mr. Tamura hadn't started it →

235
00:14:49,756 --> 00:14:52,692
I was planning on getting away with it without saying anything.

236
00:14:52,759 --> 00:14:55,128
(Ryoko) I see.

237
00:14:55,195 --> 00:14:58,632
(Luna) Bubbly-chan can't meet Mami-san →

238
00:14:58,698 --> 00:15:02,636
It's because I think it's important.

239
00:15:02,702 --> 00:15:08,208
I don't want to break up the relationship.I'm scared of being rejected.

240
00:15:11,711 --> 00:15:16,650
(Ryoko) I guess I said something thoughtless...

241
00:15:16,716 --> 00:15:18,151
(Luna) Ugh.

242
00:15:18,218 --> 00:15:22,222
I think Bubbly-chan understands Ryoko's kindness.

243
00:15:23,723 --> 00:15:27,661
But it's a sensitive topic →

244
00:15:27,727 --> 00:15:31,665
Please keep an eye on Bubbly-chan.

245
00:15:31,731 --> 00:15:34,167
(Ryoko) Yes, I understand.

246
00:15:34,234 --> 00:15:38,672
>> The cause of death of the security guard was blood loss due to being stabbed in the abdomen with a knife.

247
00:15:38,738 --> 00:15:41,174
Techniques for hacking security systems →

248
00:15:41,241 --> 00:15:44,177
A series of jewelry store thefts happening around Roppongi →

249
00:15:44,244 --> 00:15:46,179
It's likely related.

250
00:15:46,246 --> 00:15:48,181
The video of Hoshi captured inside the store is →

251
00:15:48,248 --> 00:15:51,184
He looks a lot like the serial thief that the Third Division is chasing.

252
00:15:51,251 --> 00:15:53,253
(Tamura) Is it the same culprit...?

253
00:15:56,189 --> 00:15:58,625
(operation sound)

254
00:15:58,692 --> 00:16:17,143
♪～

255
00:16:17,210 --> 00:16:20,647
(Weather Caster) In addition to "Anne of Green Gables" suites at this hotel →

256
00:16:20,714 --> 00:16:24,651
Various events are also held in the event space.

257
00:16:24,718 --> 00:16:26,653
Today from 3pm...

258
00:16:26,720 --> 00:16:29,656
(Monitor) Jewelry Festa that collects rare gems from around the world →

259
00:16:29,723 --> 00:16:33,660
It seems that it will be held, so if you don't have plans yet...

260
00:16:33,727 --> 00:16:37,230
You should definitely go out and check it out... (Ryoko) As expected, it's a popular hotel.

261
00:16:39,733 --> 00:16:42,168
Bubbly-chan, please wait.

262
00:16:42,235 --> 00:16:45,171
(Bubbly) Ryoko-san, thank you for going out of your way. (Ryoko) Uh-huh.

263
00:16:45,238 --> 00:16:47,674
It's chic today.

264
00:16:47,741 --> 00:16:51,177
>>This is the only inconspicuous clothing I have.

265
00:16:51,244 --> 00:16:53,613
(Ryoko) Oh, the party starts at 2 o'clock?

266
00:16:53,680 --> 00:16:55,615
>>Yes.

267
00:16:55,682 --> 00:16:58,118
Ah, I'm so nervous~

268
00:16:58,184 --> 00:17:00,620
(Ryoko) First, let's eat something sweet and calm down.

269
00:17:00,687 --> 00:17:02,622
(footsteps)

270
00:17:02,689 --> 00:17:05,125
(Ryoko) Ah, Mom!

271
00:17:05,191 --> 00:17:07,127
(Bubbly) What's wrong?

272
00:17:07,193 --> 00:17:12,198
(Luna) I happened to be nearby, so I came to eat Anne's sweets.

273
00:17:13,700 --> 00:17:16,703
(Ryoko) I see. Then let's all eat.

274
00:17:20,206 --> 00:17:23,143
(Ryoko) I came here because I was worried about Bubbly-chan.

275
00:17:23,209 --> 00:17:26,212
>> Because it's kind of kind.

276
00:17:28,214 --> 00:17:30,717
Which is the lounge?

277
00:17:41,227 --> 00:17:43,229
(Mami) Um, sorry.

278
00:17:45,732 --> 00:17:47,167
yes.

279
00:17:47,233 --> 00:17:49,736
What floor was the bride's room on?

280
00:17:52,238 --> 00:17:53,673
a….

281
00:17:55,175 --> 00:17:58,111
Ah...it'll be on the third floor over there.

282
00:17:58,178 --> 00:18:01,114
Thank you very much for your help today.

283
00:18:01,181 --> 00:18:03,183
(Kitahara) Thank you very much.

284
00:18:06,686 --> 00:18:09,122
I was surprised...

285
00:18:09,189 --> 00:18:13,126
(Luna) I'm sure the hotel staff can see it too.

286
00:18:13,193 --> 00:18:15,628
(Tamura) Have you seen this man?

287
00:18:15,695 --> 00:18:18,131
Khaki hoodie and black cargo pants →

288
00:18:18,198 --> 00:18:20,633
I have a silver suitcase.

289
00:18:20,700 --> 00:18:24,137
>> Ah, I guess it's the guy you picked up earlier. (Miyashita) Where did you get off?

290
00:18:24,204 --> 00:18:26,639
I think it was about an hour ago at Hotel Verdia.

291
00:18:26,706 --> 00:18:28,641
(Tamura) Can I have a look at your drive record?

292
00:18:28,708 --> 00:18:32,645
(Bubbly) Casablanca. (Ryoko) Wow, I want to go.

293
00:18:32,712 --> 00:18:35,148
Ah, but it's over. (Ryoko: Bubbly) Hahaha...

294
00:18:35,215 --> 00:18:37,650
(Ryoko) Huh? Hey, what floor was the lounge on?

295
00:18:37,717 --> 00:18:40,720
>>22nd floor. (Ryoko) Wow! As expected!

296
00:18:42,722 --> 00:18:44,657
(Employee) Oh, customer, I'm sorry.

297
00:18:44,724 --> 00:18:47,660
We are currently conducting regular inspections of our equipment.

298
00:18:47,727 --> 00:18:50,663
You can leave your luggage at the front desk.

299
00:18:50,730 --> 00:18:53,600
(Bubbly) Oh, that's amazing! (Ryoko) So cute!

300
00:18:53,666 --> 00:18:56,102
Ah, strawberries... (Bubbly) Huh, looks delicious!

301
00:18:56,169 --> 00:18:59,105
(Ryoko) Ah! Anne's costume? >> Ah...

302
00:18:59,172 --> 00:19:01,608
(Ryoko) So cute...｡

303
00:19:01,674 --> 00:19:05,111
Wow, so nice!

304
00:19:05,178 --> 00:19:06,613
(Luna) Ah.

305
00:19:06,679 --> 00:19:09,682
>> Oh? Luna!

306
00:19:13,686 --> 00:19:16,623
Huh? (Ryoko) What, Kominato-san!?

307
00:19:16,689 --> 00:19:19,192
>> Aha... Hello.

308
00:19:20,693 --> 00:19:25,131
I'm so happy! It's my first time meeting Luna's friends.

309
00:19:25,198 --> 00:19:28,635
I have always been very grateful to Luna.

310
00:19:28,701 --> 00:19:33,139
Are you sorry for the inconvenience? This kid is surprisingly missing.

311
00:19:33,206 --> 00:19:35,642
(Luna) I don't want you to tell me.

312
00:19:35,708 --> 00:19:38,144
>> He is a very reliable person.

313
00:19:38,211 --> 00:19:40,146
(Ryoko) It's fun to be with you.

314
00:19:40,213 --> 00:19:44,150
>> Hey, that's great!

315
00:19:44,217 --> 00:19:48,154
(Ryoko) Ah, I did it! Even though I'm going somewhere...

316
00:19:48,221 --> 00:19:50,156
>>Are you okay? (Ryoko) Ah, it's okay.

317
00:19:50,223 --> 00:19:52,659
>> Cherry stains are difficult to remove, aren't they?

318
00:19:52,725 --> 00:19:55,662
(Ryoko) It's okay, I'll take out the cleaning when I get home.

319
00:19:55,728 --> 00:20:00,166
>> Well, this is what we call a girls' night out.

320
00:20:00,233 --> 00:20:03,670
(Tamura) Well, thank you very much. (Kominato) Huh?

321
00:20:03,736 --> 00:20:05,672
(Tamura) Huh?

322
00:20:05,738 --> 00:20:09,676
>> Ah! Maybe Tamura-kun?

323
00:20:09,742 --> 00:20:11,744
(Tamura) Ah...

324
00:20:13,246 --> 00:20:18,184
>> It's amazing that you're a detective. (Tamura) No, no...

325
00:20:18,251 --> 00:20:21,688
>> How are your parents? (Luna) Mother.

326
00:20:21,754 --> 00:20:25,692
>> Ah, sorry, I just felt nostalgic.

327
00:20:25,758 --> 00:20:29,696
(Tamura) No, I'm glad to see you again after such a long time.

328
00:20:29,762 --> 00:20:32,699
(Luna) So what happened today?

329
00:20:32,765 --> 00:20:34,200
(Tamura) Ah…｡

330
00:20:34,267 --> 00:20:37,203
Haven't you seen this man?

331
00:20:37,270 --> 00:20:39,706
(Ryoko) What is this person?

332
00:20:39,772 --> 00:20:41,207
(Tamura) Ah...｡

333
00:20:41,274 --> 00:20:43,710
(Luna) Now, the hallway on the right side of the front desk is →

334
00:20:43,776 --> 00:20:47,714
The road is closed due to regular equipment inspection.

335
00:20:47,780 --> 00:20:51,718
But at noon on a holiday, when there are the most customers →

336
00:20:51,784 --> 00:20:54,654
It's unnatural to have periodic inspections.

337
00:20:54,721 --> 00:20:58,658
In other words, there is a sudden problem that cannot be told to the customer.

338
00:20:58,725 --> 00:21:02,662
At the end of the hallway is a locker room for valuables.

339
00:21:02,729 --> 00:21:07,166
If there's any trouble going on there, is it theft?

340
00:21:07,233 --> 00:21:09,168
(Tamura) You're still as helpful as ever~｡

341
00:21:09,235 --> 00:21:11,170
>> What's the trick?

342
00:21:11,237 --> 00:21:13,673
(Tamura) Electronic locker for valuables was hacked →

343
00:21:13,740 --> 00:21:16,175
All lockers were opened. (Camera shutter sound)

344
00:21:16,242 --> 00:21:19,178
(Tamura) In addition to the jewelry that was planned to be used at today's Jewelry Festa →

345
00:21:19,245 --> 00:21:23,182
It appears that all valuables left by regular customers were destroyed.

346
00:21:23,249 --> 00:21:26,185
(Luna) Mr. Tamura of the First Investigative Division is working →

347
00:21:26,252 --> 00:21:28,688
It probably happened around here the other day →

348
00:21:28,755 --> 00:21:33,192
A jewelry store robbery and murder case is involved.

349
00:21:33,259 --> 00:21:36,195
(Tamura) It's so sharp.

350
00:21:36,262 --> 00:21:39,699
>> Does that mean the hotel theft was the same crime? (Tamura) Yes.

351
00:21:39,766 --> 00:21:43,703
It's very likely that they do, since the methods are the same.

352
00:21:43,770 --> 00:21:46,706
(Luna) Jewelry Festa was widely announced →

353
00:21:46,773 --> 00:21:48,708
It's no surprise that I'm being targeted.

354
00:21:48,775 --> 00:21:50,710
(Tamura) Where Hoshi entered the hotel →

355
00:21:50,777 --> 00:21:53,212
I just checked it with a camera.

356
00:21:53,279 --> 00:21:55,648
So far, there is no evidence that he left.

357
00:21:55,715 --> 00:21:59,152
Investigators are now manning all entrances and exits.

358
00:21:59,218 --> 00:22:02,155
>> If you need any help, let me know and I'll be waiting here.

359
00:22:02,221 --> 00:22:05,658
(Tamura) Yes, everyone, please be careful just in case.

360
00:22:05,725 --> 00:22:07,727
(Miyashita) Mr. Tamura.

361
00:22:08,728 --> 00:22:10,730
(Tamura) Now, excuse me.

362
00:22:12,732 --> 00:22:17,170
(Ryoko) Eh, in other words, someone who might be a robber and murderer →

363
00:22:17,236 --> 00:22:20,173
You mean you're somewhere in this hotel, right?

364
00:22:20,239 --> 00:22:24,677
>>What should I do if something happens to Mami...

365
00:22:24,744 --> 00:22:28,681
I'll go in a bit. (Ryoko) Huh? Oh, Bubbly-chan?

366
00:22:28,748 --> 00:22:32,251
Ah... excuse me.

367
00:22:33,753 --> 00:22:36,756
(Luna) Mr. Kominato, please. (Kominato) Yes.

368
00:22:38,257 --> 00:22:40,760
It seems kind of difficult.

369
00:22:43,029 --> 00:22:58,411
♪～

370
00:22:58,478 --> 00:23:01,414
Now, please excuse me.

371
00:23:01,481 --> 00:23:03,483
Thank you for your cooperation today. (Kitahara) Thank you.

372
00:23:04,984 --> 00:23:07,920
Mami's room is over there.

373
00:23:07,987 --> 00:23:09,922
(Ryoko) What happened? What are you doing?

374
00:23:09,989 --> 00:23:11,924
>> No, I'm a little curious.

375
00:23:11,991 --> 00:23:15,928
After all, there might be thugs inside the hotel, right?

376
00:23:15,995 --> 00:23:19,432
What if I barricaded myself in Mami's room or Mami was taken hostage...

377
00:23:19,499 --> 00:23:22,001
(Ryoko) I think you're overthinking it.

378
00:23:24,504 --> 00:23:27,440
(Male) What time is it now?

379
00:23:27,507 --> 00:23:31,444
It's 12:32. >> Hello.

380
00:23:31,511 --> 00:24:00,907
♪～

381
00:24:00,973 --> 00:24:03,910
This day has finally come.

382
00:24:03,976 --> 00:24:07,914
I've been alone ever since my mom left.→

383
00:24:07,980 --> 00:24:11,417
Starting today, you can start a new family.

384
00:24:11,484 --> 00:24:14,987
(Kitahara) I will definitely make Mami happy.

385
00:24:16,489 --> 00:24:19,492
Mom must be happy. (2 people) Haha...｡

386
00:24:21,494 --> 00:24:24,497
I wanted Ricchan to see it too...

387
00:24:31,003 --> 00:24:33,439
(Ryoko) Bubbly-chan, let's go back now.

388
00:24:33,506 --> 00:24:36,509
I'm sure Tamura-san and his friends will catch him.

389
00:24:41,013 --> 00:24:45,451
>> Excuse me, could you bring my wife some water?

390
00:24:45,518 --> 00:24:49,522
I... I'm sorry. (Kitahara) Thank you.

391
00:24:52,024 --> 00:24:53,459
(Ryoko) No...

392
00:24:53,526 --> 00:24:56,395
(knock)

393
00:24:56,462 --> 00:24:58,898
Sorry to have kept you waiting. (Kitahara) Thank you.

394
00:24:58,965 --> 00:25:00,900
Excuse me.

395
00:25:00,967 --> 00:25:16,415
♪～

396
00:25:16,482 --> 00:25:18,417
thank you.

397
00:25:18,484 --> 00:25:22,922
(Knock) ＼This is Shimanuki, a training planner／

398
00:25:22,989 --> 00:25:25,925
(Kitahara) Thank you for your hard work.

399
00:25:25,992 --> 00:25:28,427
(Shimanuki) Actually...

400
00:25:28,494 --> 00:25:30,930
It is very difficult for me to say this, but →

401
00:25:30,997 --> 00:25:35,935
The hotel's valuables locker was stolen.

402
00:25:36,002 --> 00:25:39,438
The tiara that Mami-sama was scheduled to wear today →

403
00:25:39,505 --> 00:25:41,941
Apparently it was stolen...

404
00:25:42,008 --> 00:25:45,444
picture? (Kitahara) What? Stolen!?

405
00:25:45,511 --> 00:25:48,447
The police are investigating now... (Kitahara) No, please wait.

406
00:25:48,514 --> 00:25:50,950
That tiara is something special.

407
00:25:51,017 --> 00:25:53,452
It's a keepsake of her mother!

408
00:25:53,519 --> 00:25:55,388
(Shimanuki) Yes, that's...

409
00:25:55,454 --> 00:25:57,390
(Kitahara) I also chose the dress to match the tiara.

410
00:25:57,456 --> 00:25:59,392
It's meaningless without the tiara.

411
00:25:59,458 --> 00:26:00,893
(Shimanuki) Sorry!

412
00:26:00,960 --> 00:26:03,396
Let's start with the hotel's dress salon →

413
00:26:03,462 --> 00:26:05,398
I rented this one.

414
00:26:05,464 --> 00:26:09,402
This is an original work by a very popular bridal designer.

415
00:26:09,468 --> 00:26:12,405
It's a very expensive item made of real diamonds.

416
00:26:12,471 --> 00:26:15,975
It's not a question of price! (Mami) That's enough, Shin-chan.

417
00:26:17,476 --> 00:26:21,981
If you don't have that tiara, you don't have to wear anything.

418
00:26:25,985 --> 00:26:28,421
(sound of door opening)

419
00:26:28,487 --> 00:26:31,924
(Ryoko) Ah, Bubbly-chan, are you okay?

420
00:26:31,991 --> 00:26:33,926
>> I can't forgive it.

421
00:26:33,993 --> 00:26:35,995
(Ryoko) Huh?

422
00:26:38,998 --> 00:26:42,935
(Tamura) He looks like this. >> No, I don't really understand him.

423
00:26:43,002 --> 00:26:44,937
Excuse me.

424
00:26:45,004 --> 00:26:54,447
♪～

425
00:26:54,513 --> 00:26:56,449
(Male) Hello?

426
00:26:56,515 --> 00:27:01,020
Yes, yes...

427
00:27:03,022 --> 00:27:06,959
(Luna) Mr. Tamura, there's something I'd like you to look into.

428
00:27:07,026 --> 00:27:08,461
(Tamura) Huh?

429
00:27:08,527 --> 00:27:10,529
thank you very much.

430
00:27:14,033 --> 00:27:17,970
(Tamura) Hey, how's the investigation going? Catch the culprit quickly.

431
00:27:18,037 --> 00:27:20,973
(Ryoko) Mami-chan's precious tiara was also taken away.

432
00:27:21,040 --> 00:27:22,475
(Luna) Huh...｡

433
00:27:22,541 --> 00:27:26,045
>> There's not much time until the ceremony...

434
00:27:32,485 --> 00:27:33,986
(Ryoko) Ha!

435
00:27:36,489 --> 00:27:38,424
Huh~

436
00:27:38,491 --> 00:28:00,946
♪～

437
00:28:01,013 --> 00:28:02,948
(Luna) 《Stains that can't be removed...》

438
00:28:03,015 --> 00:28:05,518
(Ryoko) [Ah, I did it! ]

439
00:28:08,020 --> 00:28:09,955
(Luna) 《TV broadcast...》

440
00:28:10,022 --> 00:28:14,460
>> [Jewelry Festa that collects rare gems from around the world...]

441
00:28:14,527 --> 00:28:16,462
(Luna) 《Watch…》

442
00:28:16,529 --> 00:28:18,964
(Male) [What time is it now? ]

443
00:28:19,031 --> 00:28:20,966
(Luna) 《Black suit...》

444
00:28:21,033 --> 00:28:23,035
>> [What floor was it on? ]

445
00:28:24,537 --> 00:28:26,472
(Luna) 《Casablanca...》

446
00:28:26,539 --> 00:28:29,542
(Ryoko) [Wow, I want to go, but it's over]

447
00:28:32,978 --> 00:28:34,914
(Luna) We are connected.

448
00:28:34,980 --> 00:28:37,416
I think...maybe.

449
00:28:37,483 --> 00:28:38,918
(Ryoko) Maybe?

450
00:28:38,984 --> 00:28:41,420
(Luna) Could you please call Ryoko Kominato-san?

451
00:28:41,487 --> 00:28:42,988
(Ryoko) Yes.

452
00:28:46,992 --> 00:28:48,994
>>Hello.

453
00:28:51,497 --> 00:28:53,933
(Kominato) Um, sorry.

454
00:28:53,999 --> 00:28:55,434
yes?

455
00:28:55,501 --> 00:28:58,938
(Kominato) I think I left your luggage with you earlier →

456
00:28:59,004 --> 00:29:02,441
It looks like it got damaged due to some carelessness.

457
00:29:02,508 --> 00:29:07,012
I'm sorry, but could you please confirm?

458
00:29:08,514 --> 00:29:12,952
(Kominato) Yes, this was the baggage you checked in, right?

459
00:29:13,018 --> 00:29:15,454
No, that's not true.

460
00:29:15,521 --> 00:29:18,958
No, no, this is it. >> That's not true!

461
00:29:19,024 --> 00:29:23,462
(Luna) You left a silver suitcase, right?

462
00:29:23,529 --> 00:29:26,966
What's inside?

463
00:29:27,032 --> 00:29:29,468
You are not a hotelier.

464
00:29:29,535 --> 00:29:31,971
This is the criminal who stole the jewelry.

465
00:29:34,974 --> 00:29:37,910
(Luna) The first work in the "Sherlock Holmes series" →

466
00:29:37,977 --> 00:29:41,413
There is a passage like this in ``Scarlet Research.''

467
00:29:41,480 --> 00:29:44,917
“Nails, jacket sleeves, shoes→

468
00:29:44,984 --> 00:29:48,420
Pants knee shirt cuffs.

469
00:29:48,487 --> 00:29:50,422
Each one of them →

470
00:29:50,489 --> 00:29:53,425
It says a lot about the person's occupation."

471
00:29:53,492 --> 00:29:55,928
Your short sleeve length→

472
00:29:55,995 --> 00:29:58,998
Why don't the sizes match?

473
00:30:02,501 --> 00:30:06,939
(Luna) Moreover, she wears her watch facing outward.

474
00:30:07,006 --> 00:30:11,443
Hotel staff usually wear their watches facing inward.

475
00:30:11,510 --> 00:30:15,948
Plus, there's orange pollen on the cuffs.

476
00:30:16,015 --> 00:30:19,451
I think it came from yesterday's flower show.→

477
00:30:19,518 --> 00:30:22,454
Uniform with noticeable stains →

478
00:30:22,521 --> 00:30:25,958
Will the hotel staff wear it the next day as well?

479
00:30:26,025 --> 00:30:31,897
And you've been watching the police all the time.

480
00:30:31,964 --> 00:30:36,902
(Tamura) When I checked, one of my hotel uniforms was missing.

481
00:30:36,969 --> 00:30:40,906
It's the same type of thing you're wearing now.

482
00:30:40,973 --> 00:30:44,410
(Luna) If I were to write a novel based on this incident →

483
00:30:44,476 --> 00:30:46,979
It will unfold like this.

484
00:30:49,982 --> 00:30:52,918
(Luna) If I were to write a novel based on this incident →

485
00:30:52,985 --> 00:30:55,421
It will unfold like this.

486
00:30:55,487 --> 00:30:58,424
(Luna's voice) To steal the jewelry from Jewelry Festa →

487
00:30:58,490 --> 00:31:01,927
The criminal unlocked the electronic locker using his usual techniques.

488
00:31:01,994 --> 00:31:06,432
They stole all the items in the lockers and fled.

489
00:31:06,498 --> 00:31:08,934
However, at the entrance →

490
00:31:09,001 --> 00:31:12,438
There's a TV crew and a lot of hecklers.

491
00:31:12,504 --> 00:31:15,874
The criminal who has decided that it is dangerous to leave now →

492
00:31:15,941 --> 00:31:21,380
I decided to wait in a deserted place until the broadcast was over.

493
00:31:21,447 --> 00:31:23,882
However, when the TV crew returned →

494
00:31:23,949 --> 00:31:27,886
This time the police came and blocked all the entrances and exits.

495
00:31:27,953 --> 00:31:31,390
The criminal thought he couldn't escape at this rate →

496
00:31:31,457 --> 00:31:34,393
I came up with the idea of ​​escaping by pretending to be a hotel worker →

497
00:31:34,460 --> 00:31:36,895
From inside the laundry cart →

498
00:31:36,962 --> 00:31:41,900
He stole a uniform that was scheduled to be sent to the cleaners.

499
00:31:41,967 --> 00:31:46,405
But if you carry jewelry with you when you run away, you'll be suspicious.

500
00:31:46,472 --> 00:31:52,911
So I decided to take the stolen items out first.

501
00:31:52,978 --> 00:31:56,415
(Ryoko) He's a rather busy criminal.

502
00:31:56,482 --> 00:31:58,918
(Tamura) You are leaving your silver suitcase here→

503
00:31:58,984 --> 00:32:01,420
It was caught on a security camera.

504
00:32:01,487 --> 00:32:04,923
I'm currently asking the person in charge to look for it.

505
00:32:04,990 --> 00:32:07,493
>>Ah ah!

506
00:32:08,994 --> 00:32:11,930
(Male) Haha, ah...｡

507
00:32:11,997 --> 00:32:14,433
(Kominato) What? It's me!? Wait, wait...!

508
00:32:14,500 --> 00:32:18,437
(Male) Hahahaha... (Kominato) Wait, wait, wait...!

509
00:32:19,938 --> 00:32:22,875
Hmph! >> Oh wow!

510
00:32:22,941 --> 00:32:24,877
Wow, ah...

511
00:32:24,943 --> 00:32:27,379
It's no good, you're such a nuisance, don't move around.

512
00:32:27,446 --> 00:32:29,882
(applause)

513
00:32:29,948 --> 00:32:31,383
Hey!

514
00:32:31,450 --> 00:32:33,385
Haha...

515
00:32:33,452 --> 00:32:35,888
Enough? Madam, I kept you waiting.

516
00:32:35,954 --> 00:32:37,957
(Tamura) Thank you very much.

517
00:32:40,459 --> 00:32:42,394
Thank you so much Noppi.

518
00:32:42,461 --> 00:32:44,897
(Luna) You're welcome.

519
00:32:44,963 --> 00:32:47,399
>>What about the tiara? You're safe, right?

520
00:32:47,466 --> 00:32:50,402
I'm really sorry!

521
00:32:50,469 --> 00:32:53,405
(Tamura) What happened? >> Suitcase of evidence→

522
00:32:53,472 --> 00:32:56,408
Apparently, they put it on the previous flight by mistake.

523
00:32:56,475 --> 00:32:58,911
Huh!? (Staff) Sorry.

524
00:32:58,977 --> 00:33:00,412
That's a lie...

525
00:33:00,479 --> 00:33:03,415
(Tamura) Okay, I'll contact you as soon as I arrive at the office...

526
00:33:03,482 --> 00:33:07,419
>> That won't make it! When was that just a while ago?

527
00:33:07,486 --> 00:33:25,938
♪～

528
00:33:26,005 --> 00:33:28,006
(Bubbly) Wait!

529
00:33:33,512 --> 00:33:36,515
Please change your clothes. >> Yes.

530
00:33:38,517 --> 00:33:40,452
(Mami) Please.

531
00:33:40,519 --> 00:33:58,470
♪～

532
00:33:58,537 --> 00:34:00,539
Preparations will be completed soon.

533
00:34:12,551 --> 00:34:14,052
Hmm…｡

534
00:34:16,555 --> 00:34:19,558
(Ryoko) What about Bubbly? (Luna) Not yet...

535
00:34:21,560 --> 00:34:25,063
>> Ha ha ha ha...｡

536
00:34:26,565 --> 00:34:28,500
(Sudden brake sound)

537
00:34:28,567 --> 00:34:30,502
Sorry!

538
00:34:30,569 --> 00:34:34,006
Luggage... Please show me your luggage!

539
00:34:34,072 --> 00:34:36,008
It's important!

540
00:34:36,074 --> 00:34:46,518
♪～

541
00:34:46,585 --> 00:34:48,520
(Bubbly) Hahaha...

542
00:34:48,587 --> 00:34:50,088
(Ryoko) Ah!

543
00:34:52,090 --> 00:34:56,528
(Bubbly) Customer! Ha ha...

544
00:34:56,595 --> 00:35:01,033
Are you sure this is your tiara?

545
00:35:05,037 --> 00:35:08,974
Yes, definitely.

546
00:35:09,041 --> 00:35:12,478
This is a tiara that is a keepsake of my mother.

547
00:35:12,544 --> 00:35:14,980
Huh...

548
00:35:15,047 --> 00:35:18,550
Please. >> Thank you.

549
00:35:20,052 --> 00:35:23,489
(Bubbly) This time it was our fault →

550
00:35:23,555 --> 00:35:28,560
We sincerely apologize for the concern and inconvenience caused.

551
00:35:31,063 --> 00:35:34,066
Now, excuse me.

552
00:35:36,068 --> 00:35:38,070
Ricchan!

553
00:35:40,072 --> 00:35:42,074
It's Ricchan, right?

554
00:35:45,077 --> 00:35:49,014
I noticed it when they brought me water.

555
00:35:49,081 --> 00:35:52,017
I knew I was left-handed.

556
00:35:52,084 --> 00:35:54,086
〔thank you〕

557
00:35:57,089 --> 00:36:00,959
A mole on my cheek that looks like Orion →

558
00:36:01,026 --> 00:36:03,028
With Ricchan.

559
00:36:15,040 --> 00:36:18,477
Mami...

560
00:36:18,544 --> 00:36:20,546
sorry.

561
00:36:22,047 --> 00:36:26,985
I'm glad we finally met.

562
00:36:27,052 --> 00:36:28,987
Aren't you surprised?

563
00:36:29,054 --> 00:36:33,992
Well, I'm surprised she's not wearing shoes and her hair is frayed.

564
00:36:34,059 --> 00:36:36,061
That's not it.

565
00:36:37,563 --> 00:36:42,501
The me I was then and the me I am now...

566
00:36:42,568 --> 00:36:49,074
Yes, I was surprised.

567
00:36:51,577 --> 00:36:54,079
But either is fine.

568
00:36:56,081 --> 00:36:59,518
I love Ricchan and my feelings won't change.

569
00:37:02,521 --> 00:37:06,959
(Mami) She was always by my side and encouraged me.

570
00:37:07,025 --> 00:37:11,463
Thanks to Ricchan, I didn't feel lonely.

571
00:37:11,530 --> 00:37:15,534
I was able to do my best because Ricchan was there.

572
00:37:18,036 --> 00:37:19,972
(Mami) It’s me →

573
00:37:20,038 --> 00:37:24,977
I've always relied on the words Ricchan taught me.

574
00:37:25,043 --> 00:37:31,550
``The best is waiting around the corner.''

575
00:37:33,051 --> 00:37:36,488
It's a quote from ``Anne of Green Gables.''

576
00:37:36,555 --> 00:37:39,992
That was true.

577
00:37:40,058 --> 00:37:42,494
An important tiara→

578
00:37:42,561 --> 00:37:45,497
My beloved Nicchan brought me back.

579
00:37:45,564 --> 00:37:50,502
Is there anything better than this? Fufufu…｡

580
00:37:50,569 --> 00:37:53,505
Mr. Ritsu.

581
00:37:53,572 --> 00:37:57,509
Thank you for Mami.

582
00:37:57,576 --> 00:38:02,514
No, it's for me.

583
00:38:06,018 --> 00:38:10,455
Mami is my dream.

584
00:38:10,522 --> 00:38:18,463
♪～

585
00:38:18,530 --> 00:38:21,033
(Mami) [Read this]

586
00:38:24,036 --> 00:38:28,040
Mami will be a happy bride.

587
00:38:30,542 --> 00:38:33,979
Because it's my dream.

588
00:38:34,046 --> 00:38:36,548
It's my wish.

589
00:38:39,551 --> 00:38:44,556
So, will you listen to my wish?

590
00:38:47,059 --> 00:38:51,563
I want you to attend the wedding.

591
00:38:53,565 --> 00:38:56,001
but….

592
00:38:56,068 --> 00:38:58,437
If Mami was looked at strangely...

593
00:38:58,503 --> 00:39:04,443
I don't care about other people, I want you to appear.

594
00:39:04,509 --> 00:39:06,445
please.

595
00:39:06,511 --> 00:39:15,954
♪～

596
00:39:16,021 --> 00:39:18,023
Then it's decided.

597
00:39:19,524 --> 00:39:23,028
Thank you Mami.

598
00:39:25,030 --> 00:39:27,966
Hey, Ricchan, put it on.

599
00:39:28,033 --> 00:39:29,968
Hahaha...

600
00:39:30,035 --> 00:39:39,978
♪～

601
00:39:40,045 --> 00:39:41,980
Congratulations.

602
00:39:42,047 --> 00:39:43,982
thank you.

603
00:39:44,049 --> 00:39:52,491
♪～

604
00:39:52,557 --> 00:39:55,494
(Luna) Can I borrow your hotel dress?

605
00:39:55,560 --> 00:39:58,497
>> Yes, I will prepare it right away.

606
00:40:00,999 --> 00:40:05,003
Hahaha…hahaha…｡

607
00:40:11,510 --> 00:40:13,945
(applause)

608
00:40:14,012 --> 00:40:17,449
\congratulations! / (applause)

609
00:40:17,516 --> 00:40:21,453
(Mami) Thank you. >> \I hope you're happy/

610
00:40:21,520 --> 00:40:24,523
(Mami) Thank you.

611
00:40:27,526 --> 00:40:29,461
[Oh, so good! ]

612
00:40:29,528 --> 00:40:33,031
[Hahaha…]

613
00:40:36,034 --> 00:40:39,971
Ah, hehe... Thank you.

614
00:40:40,038 --> 00:40:41,973
Haha!

615
00:40:42,040 --> 00:40:44,543
(Mami) Thank you.

616
00:40:48,547 --> 00:40:50,482
(Ryoko) Bubbly-chan, that was great.

617
00:40:50,549 --> 00:40:52,984
(Luna) Yeah, I'm relieved.

618
00:40:53,051 --> 00:40:55,987
(Ryoko) Mami-chan was also a good girl.

619
00:40:56,054 --> 00:41:00,992
(Luna) The world isn't full of people like Ryoko and Mami though.

620
00:41:01,059 --> 00:41:06,064
(Ryoko) It may be like that now, but I hope it will be different in 10 years.

621
00:41:07,566 --> 00:41:10,001
>> Then let's throw!

622
00:41:10,068 --> 00:41:12,070
Se-no!

623
00:41:13,572 --> 00:41:17,509
(Mami) Wow! Hahaha...! (applause)

624
00:41:17,576 --> 00:41:21,513
(Tamura) Thank you very much for your help.

625
00:41:21,580 --> 00:41:24,015
>>It was quite interesting.

626
00:41:24,082 --> 00:41:26,518
Well, it's about time for me.

627
00:41:26,585 --> 00:41:31,022
Thank you! It was fun.

628
00:41:31,089 --> 00:41:33,091
Excuse me.

629
00:41:38,096 --> 00:41:40,031
(Tamura) Then I'll do this too.

630
00:41:40,098 --> 00:41:44,035
>>Well, let's talk a little more.

631
00:41:44,102 --> 00:41:48,039
(Ryoko) Ah! You're making your mom wait, aren't you?

632
00:41:48,106 --> 00:41:50,609
(Luna) Ah, that's right.

633
00:41:53,111 --> 00:41:56,047
(Ryoko) She's a bright and fun mother.

634
00:41:56,114 --> 00:41:59,484
(Luna) I'm already too free and I'm being swayed all the time.

635
00:41:59,551 --> 00:42:02,487
(Ryoko) Even if you say that, they seem to be good friends.

636
00:42:02,554 --> 00:42:07,559
(Luna) Well, I'm sure there are some people who are saved by that brightness.

637
00:42:10,562 --> 00:42:14,499
(Misato) Luna-san, how are you feeling these days?

638
00:42:14,566 --> 00:42:17,569
(Tamura) It's still interesting.

639
00:42:19,070 --> 00:42:21,506
My mother calls me "Luna-san".

640
00:42:21,573 --> 00:42:24,509
I'm still a "noppy".

641
00:42:24,576 --> 00:42:29,080
>> I want to treasure the name that child gave me.

642
00:42:31,082 --> 00:42:35,086
\Yes, birthday present/ \Thank you! /

643
00:42:37,589 --> 00:42:41,026
(Misato) I was confused at first.

644
00:42:41,092 --> 00:42:45,030
Coming out wasn't accepted right away either.

645
00:42:45,096 --> 00:42:47,032
(Tamura) Is that so?

646
00:42:47,098 --> 00:42:50,035
(Misato) But I studied because I wanted to understand.

647
00:42:50,101 --> 00:42:54,539
I read books, watched movies, and attended lectures.

648
00:42:54,606 --> 00:43:00,478
After about 2 years, yeah... Before I knew it, it came naturally →

649
00:43:00,545 --> 00:43:04,049
I started to think of her as a cute girl.

650
00:43:06,051 --> 00:43:08,053
(Tamura) It's a good relationship.

651
00:43:10,555 --> 00:43:13,491
(Misato's voice) Everyone is nice people~｡

652
00:43:13,558 --> 00:43:15,994
I felt relieved.

653
00:43:16,061 --> 00:43:19,497
(Luna) Maybe it's a blessing to some people.

654
00:43:19,564 --> 00:43:21,499
>> Mr. Kominato said that.

655
00:43:21,566 --> 00:43:24,502
Luna is a transgender person →

656
00:43:24,569 --> 00:43:30,008
He opened that store because he wanted to create a comfortable place to work.

657
00:43:30,075 --> 00:43:32,010
(Luna) Well.

658
00:43:32,077 --> 00:43:36,014
>> It's nice to do your best for everyone →

659
00:43:36,081 --> 00:43:39,517
Take care of yourself too.

660
00:43:39,584 --> 00:43:44,589
After all, I want my children to be happy.

661
00:43:47,092 --> 00:43:50,528
(Luna) Me too. >> Huh?

662
00:43:50,595 --> 00:43:54,032
(Luna) I want my family to be happy.

663
00:43:54,099 --> 00:43:56,601
So I won't go back home.

664
00:43:59,037 --> 00:44:04,476
>>I got my test results today.

665
00:44:04,542 --> 00:44:16,988
♪～

666
00:44:17,055 --> 00:44:21,493
Dad has been observing me for a long time →

667
00:44:21,559 --> 00:44:25,997
After detailed examination, I was told that I would have to undergo surgery.

668
00:44:26,064 --> 00:44:29,000
(Luna) This is... >> Yes.

669
00:44:29,067 --> 00:44:31,569
Success rate is 20%.

670
00:44:34,072 --> 00:44:36,508
Luna →

671
00:44:36,574 --> 00:44:42,080
Could you please come and see my father?
